spirit:busInterface.spirit:name: interrupt.irq
spirit:busInterface.spirit:description: Interrupt to other target than MicroBlaze

spirit:busInterface.spirit:name: interrupt
spirit:busInterface.spirit:description: Interrupt to MicroBlaze or to cascaded INTC

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Interrupt Status Register. For each bit up to number of periperhal interrupts: R - Reads active interrupt signal. W - No effect after MER HIE bit has been set, otherwise writes active interrupt signal. For remaining bits defined by number of software interrupts: R - Reads software interrupt value. W - Writes software interrupt value.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Interrupt Pending Register. For each bit: R - Reads logical AND of bits in ISR and IER. W - No effect.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Interrupt Enable Register. For each bit: R - Reads interrupt enable value. W - Writes interrupt enable value.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Interrupt Acknowledge Register. For each bit: W - Acknowledge interrupt.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Set Interrupt Enables For each bit: R - Reads active interrupt. W - Writing 1 enables the interrupt, writing 0 has no effect.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Clear Interrupt Enables For each bit: R - Reads active interrupt. W - Writing 1 disables the interrupt, writing 0 has no effect.

spirit:field.spirit:name: IVN
spirit:field.spirit:description: Interrupt Vector Number. R - Reads ordinal of highest priority, enabled, active interrupt.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ME
spirit:field.spirit:description: Master IRQ Enable. 0 - All interrupts disabled. 1 - All interrupts can be enabled.

spirit:field.spirit:name: HIE
spirit:field.spirit:description: Hardware Interrupt Enable. 0 - HW interrupts disabled. 1 - HW interrupts enabled.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Interrupt Mode Register. For each bit: R - Reads interrupt mode. W - Sets interrupt mode, where 0 is normal mode and 1 is fast mode.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ILN
spirit:field.spirit:description: Interrupt Level Number. R - Reads ordinal of highest priority interrupt not allowed to generate IRQ. W - Writes ordinal of highest priority interrupt not allowed to generate IRQ.

spirit:component.spirit:description: The LogiCORE IP AXI Interrupt Controller (AXI INTC) core concentrates multiple interrupt inputs from peripheral devices to a single interrupt output to the system processor.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_HAS_IPR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set when the Interrupt Pending Register is required in the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_HAS_SIE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set when the Set Interrupt Enable Register is required in the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_HAS_CIE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set when the Clear Interrupt Enable Register is required in the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_HAS_IVR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set when the Interrupt Vector Register is required in the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_HAS_ILR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set when nested interrupt support using the Interrupt Level Register is required in the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_IRQ_ACTIVE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This option should be set to define the IRQ port active logic level. 0 = Falling/Low, 1 = Rising/High.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_KIND_OF_INTR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of each bit in this option indicates the type of incoming interrupt for each bit. 0 = Level, 1 = Edge. Updates of these settings will affect C_KIND_OF_INTR parameter values.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NUM_INTR_INPUTS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of this option indicates number of interrupts input to the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NUM_SW_INTR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Number of interrupts controlled by software in addition to the hardware interrupt inputs

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_KIND_OF_LVL
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of each bit in this option indicates type of logic level for the incoming interrupt of each bit. 0 = Low, 1 = High.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_ASYNC_INTR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of each bit in this option indicates whether the incoming interrupt is treated as asynchronous or not. 0 = Synchronous, 1 = Asynchronous.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NUM_SYNC_FF
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Number of synchronization flip-flops used to synchronize asynchronous interrupt inputs

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_IRQ_IS_LEVEL
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of this option indicates the IRQ port active type. 0 = Active Edge, 1 = Active Level.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_KIND_OF_EDGE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of each bit in this option indicates the type of edge for the incoming interrupt of each bit. 0 = Falling, 1 = Rising.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_HAS_FAST
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set when the core is configured with Fast Mode Interrupt. The processor uses this setting to automatically enable the low-latency interrupt functionality. Fast Mode Interrupt is not available when selecting Single interrupt output connection.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_ADDR_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Interrupt address width with Fast Mode Interrupt.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_IVAR_RESET_VALUE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This option determines the Interrupt Vector Address reset value. It should be set to the processor interrupt vector address, which is C_BASE_VECTORS + 0x10 for MicroBlaze. Only used when the core is configured with Fast Mode Interrupt.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_ENABLE_ASYNC
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Set this option when the AXI clock is asynchronous to the processor clock. In this case the processor_clk and processor_rst inputs must be connected to the processor clock and reset, respectively. Only used when the core is configured with Fast Mode Interrupt.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: Sense_of_IRQ_Level_Type
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of this parameter indicates the IRQ port type of level. 0 = Level Low, 1 = Level High.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: Sense_of_IRQ_Edge_Type
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The setting of this parameter indicates the IRQ port type of edge. 0 = Falling Edge, 1 = Rising Edge.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_EN_CASCADE_MODE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set only when the system has more than 32 interrupt sources. This setting is applicable for all instances of the AXI INTC core cascaded together to handle more than 32 interrupts.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_CASCADE_MASTER
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set only when the system has more than 32 interrupt sources. The setting of this check box is only applicable to the primary instance of the AXI INTC core with the IRQ output directly connected to the processor. For the remaining instances of the cascaded AXI INTC cores, this check box should be left un-checked.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_MB_CLK_NOT_CONNECTED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set only when the core has the processor clock connected to its interrupt interface.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_DISABLE_SYNCHRONIZERS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This check box should be set only when the core has the processor clock connected to its interrupt interface and the core and processor clock are synchronous.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_IRQ_CONNECTION
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select interrupt output connection bus interface. Normally Bus is used when connecting to MicroBlaze and cascaded AXI Interrupt Controllers. Otherwise Single can be used when Fast Mode Interrupt is not enabled, and the target has a single interrupt input.
